keepiton_data <- read.csv("#KeepItOn 2016-2021_ 2016+2017+2018.csv", stringsAsFactors = TRUE)

countries sorted by number of shutdowns

ggplot(keepiton_data, aes(fct_infreq(country))) +
         geom_bar(stat="count")+
         coord_flip()

## Lets look at the actual cuase

ggplot(keepiton_data, aes(fct_infreq(actual_cause))) +
         geom_bar(stat="count")+
         theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=45, hjust = 1))

## here I selected a few column to to answer more specific questions:

colnames(keepiton_data)[colnames(keepiton_data) == "country"] ="region"
keepiton_data_f <- keepiton_data %>% select(year, region, start_date, end_date, duration_days, actual_cause, latitude, longitude) %>% count(region)
world <- ne_countries(scale = "small", returnclass = "sf")

keepiton_iso <- keepiton_data_f %>% 
  mutate(Iso3 = countrycode::countrycode(
    sourcevar=region,
    origin = "country.name",
    destination = "iso3c"
  ))

#join datasets
countries_off <- world %>%
  select(geometry, name, iso_a3) %>%
  left_join(keepiton_iso, by = c("iso_a3" = "Iso3")) %>%
  filter( n >0)
world %>% 
  filter(admin != "Antarctica") %>%
  st_transform(crs = "+proj=robin") %>%
  ggplot()+
  geom_sf(color="darkgrey")+
  geom_sf(data=countries_off, aes(fill= "region"))+
  scale_fill_manual(values="red")+
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
        axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        legend.position = "none")+
  labs(title = "Reported Internet Shutdowns around the World",
       subtitle = "2016~2018", 
       x = NULL, y = NULL,
       caption = "resource")+
 geom_label(
    data=countries_off,
    aes(label = name, geometry= geometry), 
    stat= "sf_coordinates", 
    min.segment.lenght = 0
  )
